Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle to sharpish turn. Rectangular stamp with caduceus symbol. Clay fine light beige; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Perhaps from Naukratis; Petrie drew several such stamps (EES XVII), Name Antimachos. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0383.09.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0800)
